`HTML

BLOCK Elements
>> This occupies the whole box - that wraps it content content
-Paragraphs (<p></p>)
-Headers (<h1></h1>etc...)
-Divisions (<div></div>)
-List and list items (ol, ul and <li></li>)
-Forms (<form></form>)

Inline Elements
-Spans (<span></span>)
-Images (<img>)
-anchors (<a></a>)

`CSS
Display: 
-block 
-inline 
-inline-block 
-none

`Position
-Static (default)
-Relative
>>Coordinates: Top, Left, Bottom, Right: 50px etc..
-Absolute
-Fixed

body{
    text-align:center; //This wil center all of its content
}

margin: top, right, bottom, Left
margin: 0 auto 0 auto -->this will center the content

*font embedding
>>If we want to have the same font everytime a user vist your website.

CSS
- em: size of font
1 em = 16px = 100% (in percentage font-size)

- rem: size of font which will ignore the val of the parent
let's say body{font-size: 200% or 2em} h1{font-size: 5.625rem} 
>the font size of the h1 will ignore the body - font size.
>>Recommended to use rem - adaptable to screen size.

float: 
>>to wrap around the Images
>>only use float if really necessary
>>do not use for Position
>>For Positioning use: Relative, Absolute (position), margin and padding